caption:
David Tennant - Shakespeare Live! From the RSC1 (2016)

NOW the hungry lion roars,
And the wolf behowls the moon;
Whilst the heavy ploughman snores,
All with weary task fordone.
Now the wasted brands do glow,
Whilst the screech-owl, screeching loud,
Puts the wretch that lies in woe
In remembrance of a shroud.
Now it is the time of night,
That the graves, all gaping wide,
Every one lets forth his sprite,
In the churchway paths to glide:
And we fairies, that do run
By the triple Hecate’s team,
From the presence of the sun,
Following darkness like a dream,
Now are frolic; not a mouse
Shall disturb this hallowed house:
I am sent with broom before
To sweep the dust behind the door.

Now the Hungry Lion Roars
By William Shakespeare (1564–1616)

From “A Midsummer-Night’s Dream,” Act V. Scene 2

title: Tumblr New Years Resolution
body:
As all my followers know, my main posting involves David. I make no apologies for that. He’s my favorite actor so he gets top promoting. However, I am resolving to show a bit more love to ‘my boys’ this year. I’ve been a huge Supernatural fan since the show first aired and have never missed an episode. I even have a yearly Black Friday tradition in which I stop off before work in the morning for a peppermint mocha frappe from Starbucks and then pick up the newest season on DVD from my local Target for $10 (Hey listen, M not made of $$ so I can’t afford it at $40 when it first comes out).

Anyway, getting off track here, the point I’m trying to make is that since it is my favorite TV show I’m going to try to post more Supernatural gifs/pics this year. There will still be plenty of David (trust me) but with a larger variety of stuff featuring ‘my boys’. And yes, I tag all my posts properly for anyone who may not be interested in seeing it on their dash which is why I’m giving you a heads up now.

Happy New Year All!
